aces of settlements, castles, buildings, various\r\nweapons, jewelry, tools found in the deep layers of the ground. Of particular\r\ninterest are materials found in the Paleolithic cave Azokh in Hadrout region,\r\nthe remains of a prehistoric human (Neanderthal). Today archaeologists of\r\nEngland and Spain, together with Armenian archeologists conduct excavations\r\nhere and discover new traces of life and activity of the ancient man.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <div class=\"col-md-6 col-sm-12\" contenteditable=\"false\">\r\n                                                <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif;\r\nmso-ansi-language:EN-US\">Artsakh mountains are rich in various monuments, petroglyphs\r\nare especially prevalent here. Their chronology is extensive and, starting from\r\nthe 7th century BC reaches 1st millennium.  Karvatchar region and the neighborhood of the\r\nvillage Tagհut of Hadrout region are particularly rich in petroglyphs.Bronze\r\nAge </span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif\">Е</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif;\r\nmso-ansi-language:EN-US\">astern Armenian provinces were inherent in the\r\nconstruction of cyclopean fortresses. In Kashatagh region, on the left bank of\r\nthe river Hochants, it remained one of the fortresses. The first state\r\nformations on Armenian Plateau appeared in the 3-1 millennium BC. </span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif\">А</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif;\r\nmso-ansi-language:EN-US\"> special place and the role was given to Van or\r\nUrartu, or Ararat Kingdom. During the reign of Argis